Idea 0 introduces Heterogeneous Document Graphs (HDGs) and SP-NRC², a powerful framework for joint reasoning over text and tables within a single document, with innovations in numerical reasoning chains, modifier grounding, and grammar-constrained graph generation. While impressive, several components overlap conceptually with existing work. For instance, the use of DAG grammars for well-formed semantic parsing is directly aligned with Paper 2, and the idea of modeling documents as graphs with structured reasoning has precedent in Paper 3 (dynamic graph frameworks for context-dependent parsing). The integration of textual and tabular data, though advanced, echoes efforts in systems like TAPAS and HybridQA, which are cited as baselines. Thus, while SP-NRC² pushes the envelope in fidelity and integration, it represents an incremental—albeit sophisticated—extension of current paradigms rather than a fundamentally new dimension.

